            <thetext>In nutshell:
I&#39;ve two tables.
The content of second table is depending on the selected row in the first table.
For modelling purpose I&#39;ve made a fill function which fills up with random datas the second table when selection changes in the first table.

The tables are wrapped in frames which change their appearance on &#39;activate&#39; and &#39;deactivate&#39; events.
The issue occurs when I set the &#39;showFocusIndicator&#39; property to false and
1. click in second table
2. click in first table to an unselected row
When the second table&#39;s filling function is called the deactivate event doesn&#39;t fire on second table and both of the wrapper frames will have appearance wich they should have when they are activated.
This issue dissapears when I set the &#39;showFocusIndicator&#39; to true.</thetext>
